For anyone who wants to learn this on guitar, here's how to play it :)

Verse: C, Am, G, F (Down strum 3 times for C and Am, 2 times for G, and once for F)

Chorus: C, Am, F, C (First chorus single down strum per chord, all other chorus' pick through each chord)

Bridge: Am, Em, F, G; C, Am, F, G (x6); Am, Em, F, G (Pick through each chord on all of these)

Hope this helps you out! If you get stuck on anything or need a little extra help, I have a video lesson for this on my channel :)

okay, i know taylor will probably never read this, but i need to thank her for something. when i was in fourth grade, i picked up her album "fearless". i instantly fell in love. when i was in fourth grade, i was depressed, lonely, and struggling. listening to some of those songs over and over made me feel not so alone anymore. i got back into singing (i sang a long before) and started writing songs. in sixth grade, i had several hospitalizations due to suicide attempts and self-harm. i started listening to some of taylor's very old unreleased songs, and i fell in love again. i am diagnosed with asperger syndrome, depression, anxiety, and gender dysphoria (i'm transgender). i am now a junior in high school, and i'm slipping back into my depression. i just recently got a ukulele, and that and taylor's new album have honestly given me hope. i feel most at home writing songs with my ukulele. it's like i was meant to do this. i finally have the motivation to post my original songs on youtube, and i'm going to eventually audition for america's got talent. and i honestly have taylor swift to thank for helping me find my calling. so thank you, taylor. thank you for making music that inspires others. thank you for being so open and honest in your songs. thank you for helping me find my passion. thank you thank you thank you. i hope to one day thank you in person, but this will have to do for now.
